      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-23T17:42:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The above function treats MultiError differently, which may lead to confusion.\nThat said, the above func only cares about *Code* which is easy to de-duplicate,\nunlike entire Statuses.\n\nMaybe nodir@ has a good thought?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 213,
        "startChar": 28,
        "endLine": 214,
        "endChar": 20
      },
      "revId": "c0b4e8d1891314a7778edbaaa49171e327106f94",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9ae19bbd_9255fc3e",
        "filename": "grpc/grpcutil/errors.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 214,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-23T17:49:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "IMO explicit \u003e\u003e\u003e implicit, especially when we face ambiguity like this.\ne.g. MultiErr contains err1 and err2. \nerr1 is annotated with a code\nerr2 is not and that is intentional, because the intention is to make it HTTP 500.\n\nI\u0027d expect [the code that chose to use MultiError] in a domain-specific way to also know what\u0027s the right way to resolve this (i.e. I am not entirely sure this generic piece of code would know what\u0027s the right thing to do)\n\nalso see my comment below",
      "parentUuid": "9f609996_d77f83d8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 213,
        "startChar": 28,
        "endLine": 214,
        "endChar": 20
      },
      "revId": "c0b4e8d1891314a7778edbaaa49171e327106f94",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0df50816_de75d4bd",
        "filename": "grpc/grpcutil/errors.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 214,
      "author": {
        "id": 1381059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-25T00:24:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e That said, the above func only cares about *Code* which is easy to de-duplicate, unlike entire Statuses.\n\nYes, this is the exact reason I have to make the behavior diverge from `Code`.\n\n\u003e I\u0027d expect [the code that chose to use MultiError] in a domain-specific way to also know what\u0027s the right way to resolve this (i.e. I am not entirely sure this generic piece of code would know what\u0027s the right thing to do)\n\nCan\u0027t agree more.\n\nSo if this function doesn\u0027t have special logic for multi-error, and based on the other comment from Nodir that it is not ideal to support the code tag. Should we just directly call `status.FromError(errors.Unwrap(err))` at the application site instead of providing a helper function here? WDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "9ae19bbd_9255fc3e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 213,
        "startChar": 28,
        "endLine": 214,
        "endChar": 20
      },
      "revId": "c0b4e8d1891314a7778edbaaa49171e327106f94",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "cd2f793e_24fb70ef",
        "filename": "grpc/grpcutil/errors.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 214,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-25T23:49:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think status.FromError(errors.Unwrap(err)) straight inside the CV is good enough: CV code knows that exactly one RPC was called. There is no reason to worry about MultiError or Tags.",
      "parentUuid": "0df50816_de75d4bd",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 213,
        "startChar": 28,
        "endLine": 214,
        "endChar": 20
      },
      "revId": "c0b4e8d1891314a7778edbaaa49171e327106f94",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "57689c53_2ca7ee66",
        "filename": "grpc/grpcutil/errors.go",
